## Part III: Characteristics of End-Time Players

### A. The First Beast of Revelation 13 (Verses 1-10)

Scripture never directly names this entity but provides extensive identifying characteristics:

**Origin Characteristics:**
- *"Rise up out of the sea"* (v.1) — Sea = "peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues" (Revelation 17:15). Arises from populated, established civilizations
- *"Seven heads and ten horns"* — Direct link to Daniel 7's fourth beast (Rome) and its fragmentation

**Composite Nature:**
- *"Like unto a leopard"* — Greece (Daniel 7:6)
- *"Feet of a bear"* — Medo-Persia (Daniel 7:5)
- *"Mouth of a lion"* — Babylon (Daniel 7:4)

This indicates an entity that **absorbs and perpetuates elements of all preceding world empires** — a successor power to pagan Rome that carries forward Babylonian, Persian, and Greek characteristics.

**Behavioral Characteristics:**
| Verse | Characteristic | Interpretive Significance |
|-------|---------------|--------------------------|
| v.2 | "The dragon gave him his power, and his seat, and great authority" | Direct satanic empowerment; occupies the dragon's former "seat" (throne city) |
| v.3 | "One of his heads as it were wounded to death; and his deadly wound was healed" | Historical near-extinction followed by recovery |
| v.3 | "All the world wondered after the beast" | Global admiration and following |
| v.4 | "They worshipped the dragon which gave power unto the beast" | Worship of Satan through worship of this power |
| v.5 | "A mouth speaking great things and blasphemies" | Claims and titles that belong only to God |
| v.5 | "Power was given unto him to continue forty and two months" | 42 months = 1,260 days = time, times, and half a time = 1,260 years (day-year principle) |
| v.6 | "Blaspheme his name, and his tabernacle, and them that dwell in heaven" | Claims priestly/mediatorial functions; attacks heavenly sanctuary ministry |
| v.7 | "Make war with the saints, and to overcome them" | Persecuting power with authority over believers |
| v.7 | "Power over all kindreds, and tongues, and nations" | Universal jurisdictional claims |
| v.8 | "All that dwell upon the earth shall worship him" | Universal religious obeisance |

**The Deadly Wound and Its Healing (v.3):**
This is a defining characteristic — a historical period of apparent destruction followed by remarkable recovery. The wound comes by "a sword" (v.14), indicating governmental/military action against this power.

**Revelation 13:10 — The Lex Talionis:**
*"He that leadeth into captivity shall go into captivity: he that killeth with the sword must be killed with the sword. Here is the patience and the faith of the saints."*

**Characteristics:**
- The first beast leads others into captivity — and itself goes into captivity
- It kills with the sword — and is wounded by the sword
- This is the "patience and faith of the saints" — they wait for God's justice

### B. The Daniel 7 Little Horn — Complete Characteristics

Daniel 7 provides additional characteristics of the same power:

| Reference | Characteristic | Significance |
|-----------|---------------|--------------|
| Dan 7:8 | "Eyes like the eyes of man" | Human intelligence directing it |
| Dan 7:8 | "A mouth speaking great things" | Blasphemous claims |
| Dan 7:8, 20, 24 | "Before whom three fell... three of the first horns plucked up by the roots" | Uproots/subdues three of the ten kingdoms |
| Dan 7:20 | "Look was more stout than his fellows" | Prominence among the ten; appears greater |
| Dan 7:21 | "Made war with the saints, and prevailed against them" | Persecuting power |
| Dan 7:25 | **"Think to change times and laws"** | **Attempts to alter God's times (Sabbath) and law (the Ten Commandments)** |
| Dan 7:25 | "Wear out the saints of the Most High" | Persecution through attrition; long-duration pressure |
| Dan 7:25 | "Time and times and the dividing of time" | 3½ prophetic years = 1,260 day-years |
| Dan 7:25 | "Given into his hand" | Saints temporarily under his authority |

**The critical characteristic: "Think to change times and laws"** — This power presumes to modify what God has established, particularly His law and His appointed times.

### C. The Second Beast of Revelation 13 (Verses 11-18)

**Origin Characteristics:**
- *"Coming up out of the earth"* (v.11) — Contrast to the first beast's "sea" origin. Arises from a sparsely populated region, a "wilderness" area
- Timing: Appears as the first beast receives its wound and "goes into captivity" (v.10)

**Appearance vs. Reality:**
- *"Two horns like a lamb"* (v.11) — Lamb-like appearance: Christ-like, gentle, peaceful
- **Two horns WITHOUT crowns** — Unlike the first beast's crowned horns; non-monarchical; republican
- *"Spake as a dragon"* (v.11) — Dragon speech: satanic legislative/decreeing power

**Key Principle: "Speak" = Legislate**

The Hebrew conception of "speaking" in relation to powers involves authoritative decree. Daniel 3 and Daniel 6 demonstrate this:

- Daniel 3: Nebuchadnezzar "made a decree" (spoke) requiring worship of the image on pain of death
- Daniel 6: Darius "signed the writing and the decree" (spoke) prohibiting prayer to any god except himself

When the second beast "spake as a dragon," it indicates this lamb-like power will eventually **legislate persecution** — using law to compel worship and punish dissenters.

**Functional Characteristics:**
| Verse | Action | Interpretive Significance |
|-------|--------|--------------------------|
| v.12 | "Exerciseth all the power of the first beast before him" | Uses identical coercive methods |
| v.12 | "Causeth the earth and them which dwell therein to worship the first beast" | Promotes/enforces the first beast's religious claims |
| v.13 | "Doeth great wonders, so that he maketh fire come down from heaven" | Miraculous displays; counterfeit divine approval |
| v.14 | "Deceiveth them that dwell on the earth by the means of those miracles" | Deception is primary mode of operation |
| v.14 | "Saying to them that dwell on the earth, that they should make an image to the beast" | Initiates image-making; democratic process ("them that dwell") |
| v.15 | "He had power to give life unto the image of the beast" | Animates/empowers the image to function |
| v.15 | "That the image of the beast should both speak" | The image itself legislates — creates laws |
| v.15 | "Cause that as many as would not worship the image of the beast should be killed" | Death penalty for non-compliance |
| v.16-17 | "Causeth all... to receive a mark... that no man might buy or sell" | Economic enforcement through commercial exclusion |

**Connection to Revelation 12:16:**
*"And the earth helped the woman, and the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed up the flood which the dragon cast out of his mouth."*

The "earth" that helped the woman (the church fleeing persecution) is the same "earth" from which the second beast arises. Initially protective, this power eventually transforms.

### D. The Number of the Beast: 666

**Revelation 13:18** — *"Here is wisdom. Let him that hath understanding count the number of the beast: for it is the number of a man; and his number is Six hundred threescore and six."*

**Characteristics:**
- "Here is wisdom" — Requires discernment to understand
- "Let him that hath understanding count" — Calculation is involved
- "The number of a man" — Connected to a specific human title or name
- "Six hundred threescore and six" — 666

The invitation to "count" indicates this is solvable by those who seek wisdom.

### E. The Image of the Beast

The "image" is not merely a statue but a **functional replica** — something that reproduces the essential characteristics of the first beast:

1. **Church-state union** (the first beast's defining feature: religious power wielding civil authority)
2. **Compulsory worship** backed by governmental enforcement
3. **The image "speaks"** — it legislates, creates binding decrees

Daniel 3 provides the typology: Nebuchadnezzar's image required universal worship on penalty of death. The end-time image reproduces this pattern.

### F. The Dragon

**Revelation 12:9** — *"And the great dragon was cast out, that old serpent, called the Devil, and Satan, which deceiveth the whole world"*

Revelation directly names this power: Satan himself. But in prophetic symbology, the dragon also represents:

- Pagan Rome (Matthew 2 — Herod's attempt to kill the Christ child while Rome ruled)
- Any governmental system directly wielded as Satan's instrument
- The ultimate power behind all earthly persecuting entities

**The Dragon's Defining Characteristic:** *"Deceiveth the whole world"* (12:9)

### G. The Man of Sin / Son of Perdition

**2 Thessalonians 2:3-4** provides characteristics without naming:

| Characteristic | Scriptural Description | Interpretive Significance |
|----------------|----------------------|--------------------------|
| Title | "Man of sin" | Sin personified in a system/office |
| Title | "Son of perdition" | Same title as Judas (John 17:12); betrayer from within |
| Action | "Opposeth and exalteth himself above all that is called God" | Claims supremacy over all religions |
| Action | "Sitteth in the temple of God" | Occupies God's place in His church |
| Claim | "Shewing himself that he is God" | Divine prerogatives claimed |
| Timing | "Revealed in his time" after restrainer removed (v.6-7) | Cannot fully manifest until a hindering power is removed |
| Method | "After the working of Satan with all power and signs and lying wonders" (v.9) | Satanically empowered miraculous displays |
| Effect | "All deceivableness of unrighteousness" (v.10) | Comprehensive deception |

The "mystery of iniquity" was **already working in Paul's day** (v.7), indicating this is not a single individual but a system that develops over time.

### H. The Antichrist — 1 John's Characteristics

**1 John 2:18** — *"Little children, it is the last time: and as ye have heard that antichrist shall come, even now are there many antichrists; whereby we know that it is the last time."*

**Characteristics:**
- "It is the last time" — The presence of antichrist(s) indicates the last time
- "Even now are there many antichrists" — Multiple manifestations, not a single individual
- "They went out from us, but they were not of us" (v.19) — **Apostasy from within the church**

**1 John 2:22** — *"Who is a liar but he that denieth that Jesus is the Christ? He is antichrist, that denieth the Father and the Son."*

**Characteristics:**
- Denies Jesus is the Christ
- Denies the Father and the Son
- A "liar" — deception is fundamental

**1 John 4:2-3** — *"Hereby know ye the Spirit of God: Every spirit that confesseth that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is of God: And every spirit that confesseth not that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit of antichrist, whereof ye have heard that it should come; and even now already is it in the world."*

**Characteristics:**
- Does not confess Jesus Christ is come in the flesh
- The spirit of antichrist was "already in the world" in John's day
- It is a spirit — a system of thought, not merely a person

**2 John 7** — *"For many deceivers are entered into the world, who confess not that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh. This is a deceiver and an antichrist."*

**Characteristics:**
- "Many deceivers" — numerous, not singular
- Denial of the incarnation

### I. Babylon the Great

**Revelation 17-18** characterizes without naming directly:

**Religious Identity:**
- *"MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH"* (17:5)
- "Mother" indicates originating system from which others derive
- "Harlots" (plural) — daughter systems sharing her characteristics
- "Mystery" — claim to esoteric religious knowledge

**Political Relationships:**
- *"Sitteth upon many waters"* (17:1) — Rules over "peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues" (17:15)
- *"Kings of the earth have committed fornication"* (17:2) — Illicit church-state unions
- *"Reigneth over the kings of the earth"* (17:18) — Political supremacy

**Economic Characteristics (Revelation 18):**
- Merchants enriched through her (18:3)
- *"The merchandise of gold, and silver, and precious stones... and slaves, and souls of men"* (18:12-13)
- Global commercial system intertwined with her existence

**Identifying Markers:**
- *"The woman was arrayed in purple and scarlet colour"* (17:4) — Official vestments
- *"Decked with gold and precious stones and pearls"* (17:4) — Immense wealth display
- *"Seven heads are seven mountains, on which the woman sitteth"* (17:9) — Geographic location
- *"Drunken with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus"* (17:6) — Persecuting history

**The Three-Part Babylon (Revelation 16:13, 19):**

Revelation 16:13 reveals the final coalition: *"Three unclean spirits like frogs come out of the mouth of the dragon, and out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false prophet."*

Then 16:19: *"The great city was divided into three parts."*

This indicates Babylon in its final form is a **tripartite alliance**:
1. **The Dragon** — Spiritualism/paganism/occult power
2. **The Beast** — Papal Rome and allied apostate Christianity
3. **The False Prophet** — Apostate Protestantism (the second beast having fully transformed)

### J. Gog and Magog — Ezekiel 38-39

**Ezekiel 38:8** — *"After many days thou shalt be visited: in the latter years thou shalt come into the land that is brought back from the sword, and is gathered out of many people, against the mountains of Israel"*

**Ezekiel 38:16** — *"And thou shalt come up against my people of Israel, as a cloud to cover the land; it shall be in the latter days"*

**Characteristics of Gog and the Coalition:**
- Occurs in "the latter years" and "the latter days"
- Comes from "the north parts" (Ezek 38:15; 39:2)
- Coalition includes: Persia, Ethiopia, Libya, Gomer, Togarmah (Ezek 38:5-6)
- Attacks Israel "as a cloud to cover the land"
- Attacks "the land that is brought back from the sword" — restored Israel
- Attacks those "gathered out of many people"
- God fights against them directly (Ezek 38:18-22)
- Destruction includes pestilence, blood, rain, hailstones, fire, brimstone (Ezek 38:22)

**Revelation 20:8** connects Gog and Magog to the post-millennial final deception.

