## Part IV: Characteristics of End-Time Events

### A. The Abomination of Desolation

**Matthew 24:15** — *"When ye therefore shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, stand in the holy place, (whoso readeth, let him understand:)"*

Christ's parenthetical — "whoso readeth, let him understand" — signals that this requires careful study of Daniel to identify.

**Daniel 9:27** — *"For the overspreading of abominations he shall make it desolate"*
**Daniel 11:31** — *"They shall place the abomination that maketh desolate"*
**Daniel 12:11** — *"From the time that... the abomination that maketh desolate set up"*

Characteristics:
- Something "placed" or "set up" — an institution or system, not a single event
- Connected to the cessation of the "daily" (true worship/mediation)
- Results in "desolation" — spiritual emptiness where truth once stood
- Involves taking away and substituting — counterfeit for genuine

### B. The Mark of the Beast

**Revelation 13:16-17** — *"And he causeth all, both small and great, rich and poor, free and bond, to receive a mark in their right hand, or in their foreheads: And that no man might buy or sell, save he that had the mark, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name."*

**Characteristics of the Mark:**
- Universal application ("all")
- Cross-class enforcement (social status irrelevant)
- Located in "forehead" (intellectual assent/belief) OR "right hand" (actions/works)
- Economic enforcement mechanism ("buy or sell")
- Alternative to the "seal of God" in foreheads (Revelation 7:3)

**Contrast with the Seal of God:**
- The seal is in the **forehead only** — requires genuine intellectual/spiritual commitment
- The mark can be in forehead OR hand — compliance without conviction suffices
- This reflects forced vs. willing worship

**Connection to Sabbath/Worship:**
The mark involves **worship** — "worship the beast and his image" (14:9). It is the **sign of allegiance** to the beast's authority, contrasted with the seal of God which signifies allegiance to the Creator.

**Exodus 31:13, 17** identifies the Sabbath as God's "sign" between Him and His people — a mark of creative and redemptive authority.

**Ezekiel 20:12, 20** — *"Moreover also I gave them my sabbaths, to be a sign between me and them, that they might know that I am the LORD that sanctify them... And hallow my sabbaths; and they shall be a sign between me and you, that ye may know that I am the LORD your God."*

The Sabbath is explicitly called a **sign**. The mark of the beast is the counterfeit sign of an alternate authority.

### C. The Great Tribulation

**Matthew 24:21** — *"For then shall be great tribulation, such as was not since the beginning of the world to this time, no, nor ever shall be."*

**Characteristics:**
- Unprecedented severity
- Universal scope
- Shortened for the elect's sake (v.22)

**Daniel 12:1** — *"There shall be a time of trouble, such as never was since there was a nation even to that same time: and at that time thy people shall be delivered"*

The time of trouble is **immediately preceding deliverance** — the final crisis before Christ's return.

### D. Signs in Nature and Society

**Luke 21:25-26** catalogues observable signs:
- Signs in sun, moon, and stars
- Distress of nations with perplexity
- Sea and waves roaring
- Men's hearts failing them for fear
- Powers of heaven shaken

**Matthew 24:7-8** — *"Nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be famines, and pestilences, and earthquakes, in divers places. All these are the beginning of sorrows."*

The phrase "beginning of sorrows" (ὠδίνων — birth pangs) indicates **increasing frequency and intensity** — like labor contractions.

### E. The Latter Rain and Cosmic Signs: Joel 2

**Joel 2:28-32** — *"And it shall come to pass afterward, that I will pour out my spirit upon all flesh; and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, your old men shall dream dreams, your young men shall see visions: And also upon the servants and upon the handmaids in those days will I pour out my spirit. And I will shew wonders in the heavens and in the earth, blood, and fire, and pillars of smoke. The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before the great and the terrible day of the LORD come. And it shall come to pass, that whosoever shall call on the name of the LORD shall be delivered"*

**Characteristics:**
- Outpouring of the Spirit on "all flesh"
- Prophesying by sons and daughters
- Dreams by old men
- Visions by young men
- Spirit poured out even on servants and handmaids
- Wonders in heavens and earth: blood, fire, pillars of smoke
- Sun turned to darkness
- Moon turned to blood
- **All this "before the great and terrible day of the LORD"**
- Deliverance for those who call on the name of the LORD

### F. The Day of the LORD — Zechariah 14

**Zechariah 14:1-4** — *"Behold, the day of the LORD cometh... For I will gather all nations against Jerusalem to battle... Then shall the LORD go forth, and fight against those nations, as when he fought in the day of battle. And his feet shall stand in that day upon the mount of Olives, which is before Jerusalem on the east, and the mount of Olives shall cleave in the midst thereof toward the east and toward the west, and there shall be a very great valley"*

**Characteristics:**
- All nations gathered against Jerusalem
- The LORD goes forth to fight
- His feet stand on the mount of Olives
- The mount of Olives cleaves in two
- Creates a great valley

**Zechariah 14:9** — *"And the LORD shall be king over all the earth: in that day shall there be one LORD, and his name one."*

### G. The Gospel Proclamation

**Matthew 24:14** — *"And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world for a witness unto all nations; and then shall the end come."*

The end does not come until:
- The gospel reaches every nation
- It serves as a "witness" — testimony requiring response
- This is fulfilled, then the end comes

**Revelation 14:6-12** — The Three Angels' Messages represent the final gospel proclamation:

**First Angel:** *"Fear God, and give glory to him; for the hour of his judgment is come: and worship him that made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and the fountains of waters."*
- Call to worship the Creator (Sabbath connection via creation language)
- Announcement that judgment has arrived

**Second Angel:** *"Babylon is fallen, is fallen, that great city, because she made all nations drink of the wine of the wrath of her fornication."*
- Proclamation of Babylon's fall
- Call to recognize her corruption

**Third Angel:** Warning against receiving the mark of the beast
- Most solemn warning in Scripture
- Wrath of God without mixture promised

