## Part VIII: The Final Old Testament Prophecy — Malachi 4

**Malachi 4:1-2** — *"For, behold, the day cometh, that shall burn as an oven; and all the proud, yea, and all that do wickedly, shall be stubble: and the day that cometh shall burn them up, saith the LORD of hosts, that it shall leave them neither root nor branch. But unto you that fear my name shall the Sun of righteousness arise with healing in his wings"*

**Characteristics:**
- The day burns as an oven
- The proud and wicked become stubble
- They are burned up — "neither root nor branch"
- But to those who fear God's name: the Sun of righteousness arises
- Healing in His wings

**Malachi 4:5-6** — *"Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful day of the LORD: And he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse."*

**Characteristics:**
- Elijah is sent **before** the great and dreadful day
- His work: turning hearts — fathers to children, children to fathers
- This prevents the earth being smitten with a curse
- The Old Testament closes with this warning

