## Part IX: Time-Related Markers

### A. The "Time of the End"

**Daniel 12:4** — *"But thou, O Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book, even to the time of the end: many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased."*

Characteristics of the "time of the end":
- Unsealing of Daniel's prophecies — previously sealed portions become understandable
- Greatly increased travel ("run to and fro")
- Explosion of knowledge

**Daniel 12:9-10** — *"The words are closed up and sealed till the time of the end. Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand; but the wise shall understand."*

At the time of the end:
- The wise will understand what had been sealed
- The wicked will not understand
- Purification and trial intensify

### B. The Hosea 6:2 Pattern

**Hosea 6:2** — *"After two days will he revive us: in the third day he will raise us up, and we shall live in his sight."*

Combined with **2 Peter 3:8** — *"One day is with the Lord as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day."*

And **Psalm 90:4** — *"For a thousand years in thy sight are but as yesterday when it is past."*

This creates a prophetic framework:
- Two "days" (2,000 years) of apparent death/scattering
- Revival "in the third day" (beginning of the third millennium from Christ)

### C. The Generational Limit

**Psalm 90:10** — *"The days of our years are threescore years and ten; and if by reason of strength they be fourscore years"*

Applied to Israel's restoration (1948), this suggests:
- 70 years = 2018
- 80 years = 2028

**Matthew 24:32-34** — *"Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When his branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is nigh: So likewise ye, when ye shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors. Verily I say unto you, This generation shall not pass, till all these things be fulfilled."*

### D. The 6,000-Year Framework

The creation week establishes a pattern:
- Six days of labor
- Seventh day rest (Sabbath)

Applied prophetically (day = 1,000 years):
- 6,000 years of human history
- 1,000-year Sabbath rest (millennial reign — Revelation 20)

This is not "setting dates" but recognizing the biblical pattern of seven-day weeks applied to history.

